item.description:
A new show has been added to showRSS: Star Trek: Starfleet Academy.

Star Trek: Starfleet Academy is set in the 32nd century, a time period in the far-future of the Star Trek franchise where Starfleet and the United Federation of Planets are recovering from a cataclysmic event, as depicted in Star Trek: Discovery. It introduces viewers to a young group of cadets who come together to pursue a common dream of hope and optimism. Under the watchful and demanding eyes of their instructors, they discover what it takes to become Starfleet officers as they navigate blossoming friendships, explosive rivalries, first loves and a new enemy that threatens both the Academy and the Federation itself.

item.title: ðŸ¤£ðŸŽ¬ READY AA?â€¦ACTIONNN!!ðŸ”¥ Ft. Dr. Gurava Reddy on Raw Talks With VK | Telugu Podcast
item.description:
Dr. AV Gurava Reddy returns for a wholesome second conversation that goes far beyond medicine, touching life, love, leadership, and the quiet pressures behind being a doctor in modern India.
In this Telugu podcast episode, Dr. Gurava Reddy shares his journey into becoming a renowned orthopedic surgeon, the inspirations that shaped him, and how discipline played a defining role in his career. From personal incidents like living and working in the UK, and balancing marriage, family, and an intense medical profession, this episode reveals the human side behind the doctor many know only through hospitals.
The conversation naturally moves into todayâ€™s most talked-about themes: anxiety, burnout, mental health labels, work-life balance, and why happiness is not an act but a practiced mindset. Dr. Reddy shares stories from his own life, his love story, marriage, parenting, friendships, celebrity encounters, music, and how counting blessings became a daily habit. He also explains why he limits surgeries on weekends, how he manages time with patients, and the philosophy behind giving just a few focused minutes that truly matter.
We dive deep into critical care decisions, empathy versus sympathy in medicine, ICU ethics, legal pressures on doctors, allegations, professional rivalries, and the emotional weight of loss. Dr. Reddy speaks candidly about medical negligence narratives, expectations from doctors, consumer court realities, corporate hospital challenges, and how ethics guide his decisions even under pressure.
The episode also highlights his social impact through the Sarvejana Foundation, road safety initiatives, free knee replacements, preventive healthcare, insurance awareness, and his message to young people and parents about lifestyle, responsibility, and slowing down in a hyper-convenient world.
Showing us how life is all about learning how to live fully, consciously, and with empathy, this conversation feels personal, and deeply relevant.

item.description:
Vishakha Sadhwani: COMPLETE Cloud Security Roadmap for Beginners [2026]

Most Cloud Security Engineers step into this role with a Bachelorâ€™s or Masterâ€™s degree in fields such as: â€¢ Cybersecurity â€¢ Information Security â€¢ Computer Science (though not always mandatory)
Top 4 Skills That Get You Hired Cloud Platform Basics â€“ Understand how AWS, Azure, and GCP work. Focus on their main services like Compute, Networking, and Storage.
Identity and Access Management (IAM) â€“ Learn how to create, manage, and restrict user permissions. Get comfortable with the principle of least privilege, Role-Based Access Control, and MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication).
Cloud Security Tools â€“ Practice with tools like AWS GuardDuty, Azure Security Center, and GCP Security Command Center.
Networking and Security Concepts â€“ Know the basics of firewalls, encryption, VPNs, and network segmentation.

item.description:
You tap play on Netflix, and in less than a second, an episode starts streaming.
Thatâ€™s not magic, thatâ€™s TCP/IP doing its job perfectly.
This is how it works, layer by layer.
1. Network Access Layer: This is the entry point. Your device connects to the internet using Wi-Fi or mobile data. If this layer fails, nothing even starts.
2. Internet Layer: Your device has an IP address; Netflix servers have theirs. Routers read these addresses and guide your request across the internet until it reaches Netflix.
3. Transport Layer: The video doesnâ€™t travel as one big file. Itâ€™s split into small packets that arrive in random order. Your deviceâ€™s job is to collect and organize them.
4. Application Layer: This layer handles communication rules. DNS finds the right Netflix server, HTTPS delivers the video securely, and keeps everything protected.
All layers work together so Netflix can load the UI, control, subtitles, and decode the video, so it can play the episode smoothly.
Want more easy explainers like this? Comment down the topic, and Iâ€™ll cover it in the future shorts.
